        <p>Every SEO automation pitch maps to one of four buckets. Buy by the bucket your team actually needs:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Content autopilot</strong> — theStacc, SEO Bot, Outrank, RankYak. Research → write → publish.</li>
          <li><strong>On-page injection</strong> — Search Atlas OTTO, Alli AI. Auto-deploy meta, schema, internal links.</li>
          <li><strong>Optimisation suite</strong> — Surfer, Scalenut. SERP-driven scoring + briefs.</li>
          <li><strong>Full SEO suite</strong> — SE Ranking, Semrush. Audit + rank tracking + workflow automation.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ The stack-everything trap</div>
          <p>Default advice in 2026 SEO Twitter is "stack theStacc + OTTO + Surfer + Semrush." That is <strong>$400+/mo and a tool sprawl problem.</strong> Most sites only need one or two categories. A bundle that covers content + Local + social will beat a four-tool stack for any business with under 50K pages.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 platforms</h2>
        <p>Same scope, same 90-day window, same three sites.</p>

